# Protobuf Conventions

## Package naming

```protobuf
package puchi.{domain}.v1;
```

Import path: `api/{domain}/v1/{service}.proto`

## File structure

```protobuf
syntax = "proto3";

package puchi.auth.v1;

import "google/api/annotations.proto";
import "validate/validate.proto";

// Service definition
service AuthService {
  rpc Register (RegisterRequest) returns (RegisterResponse) {
    option (google.api.http) = {
      post: "/v1/auth/register"
      body: "*"
    };
  }
}

// Messages
message RegisterRequest {
  string email = 1 [(validate.rules).string.email = true];
  string password = 2 [(validate.rules).string.min_len = 8];
}

message RegisterResponse {
  string user_id = 1;
  string token = 2;
}
```

## Naming rules

- Service: `{Domain}Service` (PascalCase)
- RPC: `{Verb}{Resource}` (PascalCase)
- Request/Response: `{RpcName}Request` / `{RpcName}Response`
- Field: snake_case (proto) → camelCase (Go)
- Enum: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`

## HTTP mapping

- RESTful: `GET/POST/PUT/DELETE /v1/{resource}/:id`
- Body: `body: "*"` cho POST/PUT
- gRPC: port 9090, HTTP: port 8080
